description.narrative: EAPR has strengthened evidence, partnerships and resource mobilization capacity to improve HEALTH/HIV Outcomes., which contributes to Child Health, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: EAPR effectively leverages and utilises resources, strategic partnerships, innovations, data and evidence to drive results for children

description.narrative: EAPRO Health continued to support countries in the rollout of COVID-19 vaccines to combat the pandemic and restore access to basic health services. This was done in collaboration with WHO and other UN/non-UN partners. The work of H6 partners in focusing on MNCH priorities, was important in promoting a more balanced effort, beyond vaccines and vaccinations at the height of the pandemic. The principal theme was one of partnerships, including work with academia to generate evidence for more informed programming. Efforts to increase the availability of financial resources, continued successfully, primarily for COVID-19 activities and less so for routine programming. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:14/03/2022
